memberdef.name: DEFINE_ERROR_FUNCTION
memberdef.initializer: template <typename... Args> \ inline auto name(const std::format_string<Args...> fmt, Args&&... args) \ -> std::unexpected<Error> { \ return std::unexpected<Error>( \ {ErrorKind::k##name, std::format(fmt, std::forward<Args>(args)...)}); \ } \ inline auto name(const std::string& message) -> std::unexpected<Error> { \ return std::unexpected<Error>({ErrorKind::k##name, message}); \ }

briefdescription.para: Macro to define error creation functions.
